{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"add494ad-639e-4099-ae2a-ea3c69cab377","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\". You can also use `=` for an exact match if you specify the full namespace (e.g., `FullyQualifiedName=MyNamespace.ReportExporterTests`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75e9b6a4-0d27-4771-8dab-c233186c123a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly without needing to look at files.\n\nBut let me glance at the files to give a more tailored answer.","outputTokens":187,"requestId":"CFDD:2D7BDE:143AB98:1792769:69EC1550"},"id":"42d3620c-6f5a-41ca-b62c-4cb3ed390d1b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:13:57.045Z","parentId":"b3183718-5eaf-4119-a5bf-f83ee2e0b354"}
